   <mods:titleInfo>
      <mods:title>Letter, 1824, July 20, V.B.M. in Baltimore, Md., to J.G.M. Ramsey near Knoxville, Tenn.</mods:title>
   </mods:titleInfo>
   <mods:abstract>1824, July 20, V.B.M., Baltimore, Md., to J.G.M. Ramsey, near Knoxville, Tenn. Expresses the writer's interest in history of the Mecklenburg Convention and gives advice on how best to record history. Also features a discussion of books. Encloses a sermon by the Rev. Mr. Duncan (missing) and discusses Rev. Duncan's admirable but controversial methods.</mods:abstract>
